rvice during the fault time window.\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'timeout\' or \'Timeout\' in all log entries, focusing on cartservice and frontend services.\\nCheck Trace: Filter trace data for entries where `service_name` contains \'frontend\' and check the `anomaly_avg_duration` value.\\nCheck Metric: Query the metric `rrt` for the component `redis-cart-0` and compare its `normal_median` and `fault_median` values.\\nCheck Metric: Query the metric `rrt_max` for the component `redis-cart-0` and compare its `normal_median` and `fault_median` values.\\nCheck Metric: Check the timeseries data for the metric `pod_network_receive_bytes` associated with pod `redis-cart-0` during the fault period.\\nCheck Metric: Check the timeseries data for the metric `pod_network_receive_packets` associated with pod `redis-cart-0` during the fault period.\\nCheck Metric: Check the timeseries data for the metric `pod_network_transmit_bytes` associated with pod `redis-cart-0` during the fault period.\\nCheck Metric: Check the timeseries data for the metric `pod_network_transmit_packets` associated with pod `redis-cart-0` during the fault period.",\n    "Fault Type: rrt, rrt_max, request, response, pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets\\nSymptom: High network latency, increased RTT, network delay spike, elevated transmission delay, increased round-trip time, elevated round-trip duration\\nRoot Cause: Component [cartservice, redis-cart, redis-cart-0] experienced [rrt, rrt_max, request, response, pod_network_receive_bytes, pod_network_receive_packets, pod_network_transmit_bytes, pod_network_transmit_packets] fault.\\nReasoning: Step 1: Check Metadata - Confirm faulty component is [cartservice, redis-cart, redis-cart-0] (From Ground Truth instance field) Step 2: Check Observation - Found keyword [latency_anomalies] in Trace data (From GT key_observations[0].subtype) Step 3: Check Observation - Found keyword [front